title: Copy of Partner Management Roles and Responsibilities

textRun.content: Purpose & How to Use This Document
This document addresses critical organizational risks identified in January 2026:
Certification approvals and partner decisions lack documentation (SOC2 liability)
Critical processes stored as tribal knowledge
CPC, CM, Sourcing, and PM have unclear ownership boundaries
PM team handling Tier 1 work that should route elsewhere
Daily operations, coaching workflows, escalation handling
Determine when to escalate vs. resolve; handoff requirements
Understand PM escalation triggers; dispute resolution path
Know when to pull PM in; coordination on strategic partners
Finance question handoff criteria; shared SOP reference
Tech support ticket flow; partner-facing tooling context
Visual showing all teams that interact with partners and at what stage
DECISION NEEDED: Confirm this map reflects actual intended state vs. current practice. Where are the gaps?
DECISION NEEDED: Tier system poorly communicated to partners. Benefits and advancement criteria need formal documentation and partner-facing materials.
3. What PM Does NOT Own (But Currently Gets Pulled Into)
Purpose: Name the work that should flow elsewhere so we can build proper handoffs
Current state: PM has no input; receives downstream consequences
urcing team currently calls without checking OTS/RMA data. This undermines performance-based tier system.
Current state: Only when partner relationship context needed
Current state: Only on escalation but escalations are frequent and hard to resolve
Current state: None (if SOPs exist and CPC is trained) but many queries still route to PM due to training gaps
Queries requiring judgment, relationship context, or policy interpretation
Create tech support ticket  route to Product
Review job history  explain or escalate
DECISION NEEDED: Accounting handoff criteria. Recent turnover created gap; PM receiving requests that were previously handled internally by Accounting.
DECISION NEEDED: Product bug routing. Who triages? What's the ticket path?
When partners escalate due to CM non-response, slow response, or disputed decisions
Current state: Partners call/text/email PM directly. PM mediates. Rarely changes outcome. Relationship strain.
OPEN QUESTION: What's the SLA at each step? Currently undefined.
DECISION NEEDED: Under what circumstances can PM override CM decision? Current practice: almost never. Is that correct?
PM as traffic cop when issue doesn't clearly belong elsewhere
Product team via tech support ticket
Route with job history and RCA
Prioritization: Stack rank by (lowest OTS rate)  (highest QTD bookings)
Job planning process, resource planning advice
Evaluate supplier network, ASL guidance, regional finisher suggestions
OPEN QUESTION: Can steps 1-3 be automated or pre-populated? Currently 100% manual.
KNOWN GAP: No formalized best practices materials exist. Partners receive verbal guidance only.
Prioritization: Stack rank by (highest RMA rate)  (highest QTD bookings)
Receiving inspection, in-process inspection, final inspection, packaging policies, VQC/documentation
KNOWN GAP: Quality failures in Salesforce show only "manufacturing error" with no specifics. RCA process inadequate.
OPEN QUESTION: RMA definition unclear internally. Current metric tracks parts that passed VQC but were rejected by customer. Should this be redefined?
Trigger: Partner eligible for tier progression, limit increase, or certification guidance
Partner requests or PM identifies capacity
Set by Xometry for Managed Partners every Quarter
Note: Sometimes these activities also include performance coaching (see 5.1 and 5.2)
OPEN QUESTION: What data/dashboards do partners see about their own performance?
Current gap: partners can't self-serve on meaningful performance insights.
KNOWN ISSUE: Partner tier system poorly communicated. Benefits unclear. Advancement criteria undefined. New partners "shocked by low price discovery ranges."
Mechanism: CPC changes Salesforce ticket ownership to PM queue
DECISION NEEDED: Finalize which query types are ready for CPC. Training status: paused due to CPC bandwidth. Alternative: train BO (Back Office) agents mid-Feb.
DECISION NEEDED: Boundary unclear. Need SOP for top 10 finance questions.
Current gap: Institutional knowledge lost in Accounting turnover.
Partner relationship context needed for no-take resolution
Partner requesting work beyond current routing
KNOWN ISSUE: Current sourcing process bypasses OTS/RMA data. PM coaching efforts undermined when underperforming partners receive work through relationship-based sourcing.
Confirm touchpoint map reflects intended state
Document tier system for partner-facing materials
When should Sourcing pull PM into no-take resolution?
Address sourcing bypass of OTS/RMA data
Define escalation criteria for active job issues
What's blocking CPC from handling Tier 1 queries?
Product bug routing and triage process
Define SLAs for escalation ladder steps
Can PM override CM decisions? Under what circumstances?
Appendix A: Capability Verification Requirements by Certification Type
Currently stored as tribal knowledge. Documentation in progress.
Check expiration date, company name/address match
PRIORITY: Document all certification approval criteria to eliminate single-point-of-failure risk.
Appendix B: Late Job Analysis Template
6. Root cause category (Capacity / Supplier / Capability / Non-Partner)
Appendix C: Partner Coaching Best Practices
Focus on systemic issues, not individual job failures
Provide actionable guidance, not just metrics
GAP: Formal best practices documentation does not exist. Partners receive verbal guidance only.
What counts as a "product issue"? Who triages? When does PM get involved vs CPC vs Product team?
What account problems exist? Who owns resolution? What's the decision tree?
What certifications/capabilities need verification? What's the approval process?
What financial issues come to PM? When do we involve accounting team vs handle ourselves?
What triggers PM involvement? How do we mediate? What are the dispute types?
PM team acts as first-line triage - not just routing, but actually diagnosing whether it's education vs. a real bug in the product
The Customer Partner (CPC) first attempts to address the user's lack of knowledge.
If the CPC is unsuccessful, the issue is escalated to the Partner Manager (PM).
The PM resolves the issue through education and resolution.
The issue is routed to the Partner Manager (PM).
The PM creates a technical support ticket.

What specific criteria does the CPC use to determine that an issue is beyond its scope ("I can't handle this")? Does this criterion simply default to "anything product-related goes to PM," or is there specialized training outlining what questions the CPC is authorized to answer?
Are there specific product-related issues that the CPC is equipped to resolve internally (e.g., routine questions about navigating the Workcenter interface)?
Account-related partner inquiries are not specific to a job but concern their overall account status, settings, visibility, or capacity on the Xometry platform.
Managing user accounts, permissions, and onboarding new team members.
Addressing performance score adjustments, including Xometry-initiated changes and removal from an outsourcing group.
Ensuring partners have appropriate visibility to the job board ("I want more work") based on their capabilities.
Handling requests from inactive partners for reactivation and overseeing performance improvement plans.
Guiding partners on advancing to the next level ("How do I get to the next level?"), including capability enhancements and new process certifications.
Note: Disproportionately high volume from Additive partners
If CPC can resolve (Tier 1) -> Follow SOP and resolve
If not -> Transfer ownership to Partner Management queue (Salesforce)
PM investigates: Check partner page, review what changed, analyze history
PM communicates findings and rationale to partner
What specific criteria differentiate Tier 1 vs Tier 2 account issues?
Process for partners who repeatedly have the same account issues?
Verification and validation of partner certifications, process capabilities, and quality systems required to perform specific types of work on the Xometry platform.
Certification Checks: Verifying compliance certifications (ISO, AS9100, ITAR) - requires legal/compliance approval
Process Capability: Assessing partner ability to meet specific manufacturing requirements
CMM Inspection: Verifying measurement capability with photographic proof required
Quality System Verification: Various quality/capability verifications
Partner submits certification or capability documentation
If compliance/legal approval needed (ISO, AS9100, ITAR)  Route to compliance team
PM Team: Initial review and approval workflow
Legal/Compliance: Certification verification for regulated standards (ISO, AS9100, ITAR)
What specific guidance exists from legal and compliance?
What are the specific criteria/documentation/review process for each certification type?
Process for expired or lapsed certifications?
Financial/payment issues that partners bring to PM team
Job related: Inquire with CM to correct ERP information or provide override approvals to accounting
Finance account related: Submit request via SF ticket or to the accounting slack channel to accounting for support resolution
Need clarity on what the PM v/s Accounting Ownership
Whats the remediation process for payment disputes?
When partners are unsatisfied with case manager handling
address core operational and communication problems:
Delayed communication/action.Incomplete or unhelpful replies/actions. Communication breakdowns due to unprofessional or negative language.
Unequal application of standards to similar issues.
Unequal application of standards to similar issues.
These issues often connect with conflicts in the
When partners suggest that its not their fault
Partner escalates to CPC or another internal team who then sends to the PM team if needed. Partner may also escalate to a PM directly.
Xomer reviews the OPC/SF case communications for context and contact CM for resolution

In the event of CM nonresponse or disagreement, escalate to the next in command in the Pod organizational structure (CM Lead -> Business Lead -> Pod VP). If PM and Pod are in disagreement, escalate to PM leadership (Manager -> VP -> SVP)
PM Team (escalation handler from Case Management Team)
How do we track repeat escalations?
How do we resolve RMA, OTS and PSS related disputes

Trend not captured by PM team
Asymmetric performance on a job despite OTS >92% in aggregate
QTD Bookings and OTS Delta from 92% to stack rank coaching candidates
RCA using salesforce (and reach out to partners sometimes)
Coach on an ideal process (best shop practices need to be documented)
Get legal and compliance buy-in before this is shared with a partner
Sharing data / dashboards (ideally should be in workcenter)

Trend not captured by PM team
Asymmetric performance on a job despite RMA <1.8% in aggregate
QTD Bookings and RMA Delta from 1.8% RMA to stack rank coaching candidates
RCA using salesforce (and reach out to partners sometimes)
Get legal and compliance buy-in before this is shared with a partner
Sharing data / dashboards (ideally should be in workcenter)

Promote Partners to a Higher Tier
Coaching on QMS and Certification gaps
